{"name":"Arcane Backgrounds","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3t20aa8en26","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. Magic#/CF_SEP/4.1. Using Magic","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Arcane Backgrounds</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>There are numerous Arcane Backgrounds avilable in the <cite>Eberron Campaign Setting</cite>. Review all the backgrounds below for a summary of what kind of heroes use them. These are the backgrounds that are available to be used and in all cases should be used instead of those presented in the <cite>Savage Worlds</cite> core rules.</p>\n<figure class=\"figure table-figure\">\n<figcaption class=\"figure-heading\">Arcane Background Summaries</figcaption>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Arcane Background</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Arcane Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)]{Aberrant Dragonmark}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Dragonmark Focus]{Dragonmark Focus (Spirit)}</td>\n<td>Heroes that has manifested an Aberrant Dragonmark that falls outside the standard marks of the Dragonmarked Houses.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Artifice)]{Artifice}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Artifice]{Artifice (Smarts)}</td>\n<td>Masters of unlocking magic in everyday objects, artificers are supreme inventors. Creating objects of all kinds that can be used to harness magic.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Divine Magic)]{Divine Magic}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Faith]{Faith (Spirit)}</td>\n<td>From priests to clerics to vassals. Any that draw their power from their faith in any of the Gods of Eberron.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Dragonmark)]{Dragonmark}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Dragonmark Focus]{Dragonmark Focus (Spirit)}</td>\n<td>A mark that is tied to certain racial bloodlines, that manifests in a standard pattern allowing the user the ability to preform certain tasks and magic.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Druidism)]{Druidism}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Druidism]{Druidism (Spirit)}</td>\n<td>Druids draw primal magic from the world itself. most druids are swathed in tradition.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Gifted)]{Gifted}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Focus]{Focus (Spirit)}</td>\n<td>The hero has innate abilities that don't fit in the any of the other magical backgrounds, such as innate racial magic, or sorcerers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Magic)]{Magic}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting (Smarts)}</td>\n<td>Heroes that are taught to draw on the raw magical energies that are ever present in Eberron. From mages, to wizards, to illusionists, to necromancers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Psionics)]{Psionics}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Psionics]{Psionics (Spirit)}</td>\n<td>Psionic powers spring from sentient minds drawing on a reservoir of mental strength to manipulate matter, read minds, and far more.&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Song Magic)]{Song Magic}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Song Magic]{Song Magic (Spirit)}</td>\n<td>Song mages, bards, or skalds work their magic through the power of their voice and musical instruments.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Wandslinger)]{Wandslinger}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Wand Magic]{Wand magic (Smarts)}</td>\n<td>An arcaneer that has been trained to use offensive wand magic in combat, without needing to master magic.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</figure>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Articles on the Use of Magic</h2>\n<div class=\"swade-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Arcane Backgrounds}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Powers Modifiers}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Powers Summary List]{Powers Summary list}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Rituals]{Rituals}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","_id":"A1nL8N0xR8N1Db1K"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_7967rzk60vt","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000","name":"1.1. Races","children":["swOEdUth0tfq0KK2","vFvpjrnzuM0wrVt6","wO7NwoTF7N5SDQZu","hn1oMCipYP2AAUOv","19QPB8nR0mJSvqR1","UljWJl3HHbV01jlE","MILhXBlwUyluGlHW","1jOSJXXd3ywrW1UR","V5WarO1p3xfmYZ6n","FnZcvTkjtICeTXZf","DvW48gwVGtE1InPo","VusJttWwYlQ8DNX2","W2jC1j3DJRf6zluC","pMnKtz1ySCDIPHms","MAOtpm7i1zWBFRzS","PGUq1EevulMlPiTk","IQcsMa3gs9uyzU1Q","sg0Tau6fSkQI7AQT","BCEYjF0hE4q7uqQ4"],"folderPath":["temp_okfc4yccund","temp_jtibz2gzdj"]}},"content":"","_id":"AaCETpZNHTgevavJ"}
{"name":"Warforged","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.yWt3PCcYjHyfqmlo"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7967rzk60vt","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Warforged</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>The warforged were built to fight in the Last War. While the first warforged were mindless automatons, House Cannith devoted vast resources to improving these steel soldiers. An unexpected breakthrough produced sapient soldiers, giving rise to what some have only grudgingly accepted as a new species. Warforged are made from wood and metal, but they can feel pain and emotion. Built as weapons, they must now find a purpose beyond war. A warforged can be a steadfast ally, a cold-hearted killer, or a visionary in search of meaning.</p>\n<h3>Living Steel and Stone</h3>\n<p>Warforged are formed from a blend of organic and inorganic materials. Root-like cords infused with alchemical fluids serve as their muscles, wrapped around a framework of steel, darkwood, or stone. Armored plates form a protective outer shell and reinforce joints. Warforged share a common facial design, with a hinged jaw and crystal eyes embedded beneath a reinforced brow ridge. Beyond these common elements of warforged design, the precise materials and build of a warforged vary based on the purpose for which it was designed.</p>\n<p>Although they were manufactured, warforged are living humanoids. Resting, healing magic, and the Medicine skill all provide the same benefits to warforged that they do to other humanoids.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Warforged Personality</h3>\n<p>The warforged were built to serve and to fight. For most of their existence, warforged had a clearly defined function and were encouraged to focus purely on that role. The Treaty of Thronehold gave them freedom, but many still struggle both to find a place in the post-war world and to relate to the creatures who created them.</p>\n<p>The typical warforged shows little emotion. Many warforged embrace a concrete purpose&mdash;such as protecting allies, completing a contract, or exploring a land&mdash;and embrace this task as they once did war. However, there are warforged who delight in exploring their feelings, their freedom, and their relationships with others. Most warforged have no interest in religion, but some embrace faith and mysticism, seeking higher purpose and deeper meaning.</p>\n<p>The typical warforged has a sexless body shape. Some warforged ignore the concept of gender entirely, while others adopt a gender identity.</p>\n<p>The more a warforged develops its individuality, the more likely it is to modify its body, seeking out an artificer to customize the look of its face, limbs, and plating.</p>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Built for War:</strong> Warforged were designed, built, and trained as tools of war. Negotiations were not part of their training, and their world knowledge off of the battlefield is limited. They do not have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} as core skills.</li>\n<li><strong>Composite Plating: </strong>A warforged is covered in tough plating made of magically-treated woods and metals. Warforged gain a +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}. Warforged are unable to wear additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{armor}.</li>\n<li><strong>Living Construct:</strong> Warforged are living constructs made from organic and inorganic matter and are capable of emotions and conscious thought. They do not need to breathe, eat, or drink, and are immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Disease]{disease}. Wounds must be mended via the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{repair}</em> power or the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} skill. Each attempt takes one hour per current @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} level and ignores the &ldquo;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{Golden Hour}&rdquo;.</li>\n<li><strong>Loyal (Minor): </strong>Warforged are trained to protect their allies in combat, and will always be the first to come to their rescue.</li>\n<li><strong>Outsider (Major): </strong>With a history of being dedicated soldiers of war, warforged have difficulty blending into post-war Khorvaire. Most non-warforged strongly dislike the sight of warforged as they stand as living reminders of the horror that was the Last War. As such, warforged have -2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls when interacting with non-warforged and are often treated with less rights that others.</li>\n<li><strong>Specialized Design:</strong> Warforged are typically designed for specific purposes. They start with a d4 in any skill based on their experiences, education, training. If the chosen skill is a core skill, it starts at d6 and the skill's maximum increases to d12+1.</li>\n<li><strong>Steel Fists:</strong> Warforged fists are @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons} that cause @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}+d4 damage.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/art/races/warforged.webp\" alt=\"Warforged\" /></div>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-rules/assets/art/warforged.webp","_id":"BCEYjF0hE4q7uqQ4"}
