{"name":"Arcane Background (Dragonmark)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_e33lugmfz55","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. Magic#/CF_SEP/4.2. Arcane Backgrounds","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<h2>Arcane Background (Dragonmark)</h2>\n<div>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Edge:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Dragonmark)]{Arcane Background (Dragonmark)}</li>\n<li><strong>Requirements:</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Novice}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} d8+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Dragonmark Focus]{Dragonmark Focus} d4+</li>\n<li><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Dragonmark Focus]{Dragonmark Focus}&nbsp;(@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit})</li>\n<li><strong>Born to the Mark:</strong> Dragonmarked heirs may take Edges that require @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Gifted)]{Arcane Background (Gifted)}. They may ignore all rank requirements for the power when this edge is taken. Finally, the heir can ignore one point of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}.</li>\n<li><strong>Race and Aberrant Dragonmarks: </strong>This Arcane Background is only available to dragonmarked races. Races with multiple choices can only ever choose to have one kind of dragonmark. Adventurers with an Aberrant Dragonmark cannot select this Arcane Background as well.</li>\n<li><strong>Natural Ability: </strong>The mark also grants a +1 skill bonus to one skill based on the dragonmark taken.</li>\n<li><strong>Backlash: </strong>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} on a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Dragonmark Focus]{Dragonmark Focus} roll causes the dragonmarked heir a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} and all currently active powers are terminated.</li>\n<li><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>2</li>\n<li><strong>Available Powers:&nbsp;</strong>Based on the dragonmark.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Playing a Dragonmarked Heir</h2>\n<p>A dragonmark enhances the user's ability to perform certain tasks. For example, the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Cannith]{Mark of Making} guides the hands of the smith, while the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Phiarlan]{Mark of Shadows} helps its bearer avoid enemies. The power of a dragonmark can also manifest in more dramatic ways. The @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Lyrandar]{Mark of Storms} can scatter enemies with a blast of wind, while the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Phiarlan]{Mark of Shadows}&nbsp;can weave illusions.</p>\n<p>No one can buy or choose to develop a dragonmark; each mark is tied to bloodlines within specific species. A dragonmark appears on a person around adolescence when put through the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Test of Siberys], though not every heir manifests the mark.</p>\n<p>Long ago, the families that carry the marks joined together to form the dragonmarked houses. Over the course of centuries, these houses have used their gifts to establish powerful monopolies. For example, only @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Lyrandar] heirs with the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Lyrandar]{Mark of Storms}&nbsp;can pilot airships. This control over vital services gives the houses tremendous power.</p>\n<p>In the past, the dragonmarked houses were held in check by the united kingdom of Galifar. But in the wake of the Last War, people wonder if any nation has the power to enforce its wishes on the houses.</p>\n<p>The adventurer has a dragonmark as appropriate to his race, and is considered a dragonmarked heir. The dragonmark grants the a power from those available to the a particular Mark. In addition a bonus to one skill used by heirs of that dragonmark. The dragonmark grants the ability to use dragonmark focus items and a power granted by that specific mark.</p>\n<p>Each time the adventurer selects the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.New Powers] Edge for this Arcane Background, the dragonmark changes into a larger, more complex pattern and increases in power.</p>\n<h3>Dragonmarks and Backgrounds</h3>\n<p>Dragonmarks are bound to certain bloodlines, and by choosing a mark, you are establishing your character's blood connection to one of the families in the dragonmarked houses. It's up to you to define your relationship to the house. Were you brought up in the house? Or are you independent from it? This is best represented by your background. Consider the following options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Agent.</strong> You have a close, ongoing relationship with your house. The house agent background is a good choice if you are actively working for the house. Alternately, you could take the noble background to reflect a blood tie to the leaders of the house.</li>\n<li><strong>Independent Scion. </strong>You were raised or trained by the house, but you've kept your independence. This means you don't have many special privileges, but you also don't have responsibilities. Guild artisan is a good choice to reflect basic house training, but you could choose entertainer for the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Phiarlan]{Mark of Shadows}, sailor for the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Lyrandar]{Mark of Storms}, soldier for the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Dennieth]{Mark of Sentinel}, sage for the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Sivis]{Mark of Scribing}, and so on.</li>\n<li><strong>Excoriate. </strong>When a dragonmarked heir defies their house, they might be cut off from their family. In the past, your mark would be flayed from your body. Although this mutilation is no longer practiced, such exiles are still called excoriates. If you're an excoriate, consider what you did to deserve this punishment. Were you a criminal? A charlatan? Or perhaps a sage who engaged in forbidden research?</li>\n<li><strong>Foundling. </strong>Your ancestors left the house long ago. You have no ties to the house and may not have known you were connected by blood before you manifested your dragonmark. As an outlander or an urchin, you might know nothing about the houses. As an acolyte or a hermit, you could have put your faith ahead of worldly things, choosing not to pursue a connection with the houses. Whatever you decide, this is an opportunity to talk with your DM about the role you'd like the house to play in a campaign. Do you want them to be your enemy? Would you prefer to avoid them completely? Or do you want to work your way into a position of power in the house, despite being an outsider?</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Dragonmark Appearance</h3>\n<p>A dragonmark appears on the skin. There are twelve known dragonmarks, each unique in design and power. A dragonmark can appear on any part of the body. One half-elf could have the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Medani]{Mark of Detection}&nbsp;across an eye, while another has it in the palm of the hand. Dragonmarks appear with vivid shades of blue and purple and shimmer or even move slightly.</p>\n<p>The character can also roll on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-tables.Dragonmark Quirks] table for their dragonmark.</p>\n<h2>Casting</h2>\n<p>Dragonmarked heirs just need to concentrate to activate the powers of their dragonmark. They do not need their hands free or speak.</p>\n<h2>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trappings}</h2>\n<p>All dragonmark powers, come from the dragonmark themselves and therefore tend to be subtle. Trappings would generally be the dragonmark growing warm to the touch and producing a soft glow. Other types of trappings can be created that should follow along these lines.</p>\n<br />\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Dragonmark Abilities and Powers</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Mark</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Race</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill Bonus</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Powers</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Medani]{Mark of Detection}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Half-elf]{Half-elf}</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} (Both @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation})</td>\n<td class=\"list-powers\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait} (not lower Trait), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal]{Detect} (not conceal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Divination]{Divination}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Enviromental Protection]{Enviromental Protection}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Tharashk]{Mark of Finding}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Half-orc], @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Human]{human}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{orc}</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival}</td>\n<td class=\"list-powers\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Analyze Foe]{Analyze Foe}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal]{Detect} (not Conceal), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{Farsight}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Object Reading]{Object Reading}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Vadalis]{Mark of Handling}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Human]{Human}</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Animal Handling]{Animal Handling} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding}</td>\n<td class=\"list-powers\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{Beast friend}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait} (animals only, not lower trait), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empathy]{Empathy} (animals only), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]{Summon Beast}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Jorasco]{Mark of Healing}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Halfling]{Halfling}</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{Healing} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival}</td>\n<td class=\"list-powers\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Accelerate healing]{Accelerate healing}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost} (not Lower Trait), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.False Health]{False Health}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{Healing}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{Relief}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Ghallanda]{Mark of Hospitality}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Halfling]{Halfling}</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}</td>\n<td class=\"list-powers\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dimensional Space]{Dimensional Space}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empath]{Empathy} (humanoids only), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{Elemental Manipulation} (air, fire and water only), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Feast]{Feast}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Cannith]{Mark of Making}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Human]{Human}</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Crafting]{Crafting} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair}</td>\n<td class=\"list-powers\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Conjure Item]{Conjure Item}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Creation]{Creation}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Legerdemain]{Legerdemain}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{Repair}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Orien]{Mark of Passage}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Human]{Human}</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding}</td>\n<td class=\"list-powers\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dimensional Leap]{Dimensional Leap}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{Speed}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]{Summon Beast} (mount only), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{Teleport}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Sivis]{Mark of Scribing}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Gnome]{Gnome}</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Lore]{Lore} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}</td>\n<td class=\"list-powers\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Magic Mark]{Magic Mark}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Message]{Message}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Secret Writting]{Secret Language}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{Speak Language}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Deneith]{Mark of Sentinel}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Human]{Human}</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}</td>\n<td class=\"list-powers\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait} (not Lower Trait), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Gift of Battle]{Gift of Battle}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{Protection}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{Warrior's Gift}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Phiarlan]{Mark of Shadow}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Elf]{Elf}</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth}</td>\n<td class=\"list-powers\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{Darkness}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]{Disguise}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Illusion]{Illusion}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Intangibility]{Intangibility}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Legerdemain]{Legerdemain}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Lyrandar]{Mark of Storm}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Half-elf]{Half-elf}</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting}</td>\n<td class=\"list-powers\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Becalm]{Becalm}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{Elemental Manipulation} (air and water only), @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Tempest]{Tempest}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Whirlwind]{Whirlwind}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Zephyr]{Zephyr}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.House Kundarak]{Mark of Warding}</td>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Dwarf]{Dwarf}</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}</td>\n<td class=\"list-powers\">@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane Protection}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{barrier}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Glyph]{Glyph}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Lock/Unlock]{Lock/Unlock}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sentry]{Sentry}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Ward]{Ward}</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","_id":"FkxXkVOSgjXDfJpj"}
{"name":"Half-giant","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{"Item":["IsbekHb4py8znJkY"]}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.vXetYPQjtecEgRPV"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7967rzk60vt","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Half-giant</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Coming from either Sarlona or Xen&rsquo;drik, they are now a true-breeding stock from the ancient Titans of Xen&rsquo;drik. Half-giants, for the most part, retain human sensibilities. They are curious, interested in cooperation and communication, and have a general tendency toward kindness. (Half-Giants are from Sarlona and Xen&rsquo;drik, talk to your DM if you want to play this race.)</p>\n<p>Perhaps the most baffling of all the races on the continent, the nomadic half-giants of Sarlona are descendants of ancient giant explorers from Xen'drik. Some say the half-giants are degenerate offspring of the Xen'drik titans, while others contend they have a mixed human ancestry.</p>\n<p>What can be said is that the true-breeding half-giants are racially inclined toward psionic ability, and this racial trait binds them into tight-knit but individually isolated bands. Half-giants refer to their groups as families, rather than tribes or clans, although few members of a family are actually blood-related. In fact, many families adopt individuals of other races, particularly psionic ones such as elans, dromites, duergar, and maenads.</p>\n<h3>Half-Giant Lands</h3>\n<p>Half-giant families wander endlessly all over Sarlona, although they rarely stray into Riedran territory. There, they are often \"assimilated\"&mdash;a process beginning as slavery. What is remarkable is the degree to which they tend to coexist peaceably with denizens of all other regions. In Tashana, where families are known collectively as the Icebinders, half-giants have a long tradition of trade and cooperation with the shifter and human tribes. The Sandstrider families of Syrkarn keep more to themselves, with occasional but minimal conflict with the humans and eneko of the region. In Adar, a handful of half-giant families called the pathadrik wander among the settlements and monasteries.</p>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Cumbersome: </strong>Half-giants aren't the most dextrous of creatures. They suffer a &ndash;1 penalty to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} rolls.</li>\n<li><strong>Fire Acclimated:</strong> Half-giants are accustomed to enduring high temperatures. They gain a +4 bonus to resist the effects of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heat]{heat} and fire. Damage from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heat]{heat} and fire is also reduced by 4.</li>\n<li><strong>Natural Brute:</strong> Half-giants have natural core strength and fitness over coordination and flexibility. They treat @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} as linked to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} for purposes of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Advancement}. The character may also resist Athletics @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests} with Strength if she chooses. Finally, half-giants increase the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Short Range} of any thrown item by +1. Double that for the adjusted @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Medium Range}, and double again for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Long Range}. If a thrown item&rsquo;s Range is 3/6/12, for example, a half-giant's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range} is 4/8/16.</li>\n<li><strong>@Item[IsbekHb4py8znJkY]{Outsider (Minor)}:</strong> Most other races are put off by half-giants due to their abnormally large size. In fact, many are at first taken for young (if strangely well-groomed) hill giants. They have -2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} as other races tend to distrust them.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} +1:</strong> Half-giants are much larger than humans, standing about 6 &frac12; &minus; 8 feet tall, increasing thier @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (and therefore their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}) by 1. This increases their maximum @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} to d12+1.</li>\n<li><strong>Stomp:</strong> With a forceful stomp of their foot, half-giants can create a wave of trembling earth. With a successful @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll, targets caught within a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Cone Template} originating from the half-giant&rsquo;s step are knocked @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{Prone}; with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, they are also @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/art/races/half-giant.webp\" alt=\"Half-giant smith showing off his work.\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-rules/assets/art/half-giant.webp","_id":"FnZcvTkjtICeTXZf"}
