Relief}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>&ndash;1</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>Removes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}; &amp; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stun} with raise.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{Repair}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>&ndash;2</td>\n<td>T</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>Restores @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} to constructs less than an hour old.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Resurrection]{Resurrection}</td>\n<td>H</td>\n<td>&ndash;20</td>\n<td>T</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>Brings the dead back to life.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Secret Writing]{Secret Writing}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>&ndash;5</td>\n<td>T</td>\n<td>Perm</td>\n<td>Disguise the contents of a written message.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sentry]{Sentry}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>&ndash;3</td>\n<td>Sm x2</td>\n<td>Special</td>\n<td>Creates a sentry to watch over an area or object.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Shape Change]{Shape Change}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>Special</td>\n<td>Self</td>\n<td>2m/R</td>\n<td>Caster takes on the form of various beings.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{Sloth/Speed}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>&ndash;2</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>I or 1m/R</td>\n<td>Increases or decreases @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Movement}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]{Slumber}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>&ndash;5</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>1H/R</td>\n<td>Puts victims to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Sleep]{Sleep}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{Smite}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>&ndash;1</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>1m/R</td>\n<td>Increase a weapon&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage]{damage} by +2/+4.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{Sound/Silence}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>&ndash;1</td>\n<td>Sm x5/Sm</td>\n<td>I or 1m/R</td>\n<td>Create or mute sound.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{Speak Language}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>&ndash;1</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>1H/R</td>\n<td>Caster can speak and understand languages.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{Stun}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>&ndash;1</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>Target is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Ally]{Summon Ally}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>Special</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>10m/R</td>\n<td>Conjures an ally of various sorts.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]{Summon Beast}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>Special</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>10m/R</td>\n<td>Conjures mundane animals under characters control.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Fiend]{Summon Fiend}</td>\n<td>V</td>\n<td>Special</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>2H/R</td>\n<td>Conjures a fiend.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Elemental]{Summon Elemental}</td>\n<td>V</td>\n<td>&ndash;5</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>10m/R</td>\n<td>Conjures an elemental.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{Telekinesis}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>&ndash;3</td>\n<td>Sm x2</td>\n<td>1m/R</td>\n<td>Moves items with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} of d10 (d12 with a raise).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Teleport]{Teleport}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>&ndash;6</td>\n<td>Self</td>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>Character teleports up to Smarts x5 miles distant.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Tempest]{Tempest}</td>\n<td>V</td>\n<td>&ndash;20</td>\n<td>Sm xMiles</td>\n<td>2d6 hours</td>\n<td>Create or dispel a storm.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wall Walker]{Wall Walker}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>&ndash;1</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>1m/R</td>\n<td>Character can walk on walls at half @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} (full Pace with raise).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Ward]{Ward}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>&ndash;4</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>2H/R</td>\n<td>Create barrier against one creature type.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{Warrior's Gift}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>&ndash;3</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>1m/R</td>\n<td>Grant target a Combat @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edge}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Whirlwind]{Whirlwind}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>&ndash;1</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>1m/R</td>\n<td>Create a whirlwind in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{MBT or LBT} that knocks targets @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Zephyr]{Zephyr}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>&ndash;1</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>1H/R</td>\n<td>Increase the wind that will increase the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Vehicle Notes]{Handling} by 1 and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Vehicle Notes]{Top Speed}&nbsp;by 25% of one ship.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Zombie]{Zombie}</td>\n<td>V</td>\n<td>&ndash;1</td>\n<td>Sm</td>\n<td>1H/R</td>\n<td>Raises and controls the undead.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","_id":"WyOQrtiOSkPWeT97"}
{"name":"Wizard","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.23nhljaxcjJ23SWE"},"cf":{"id":"temp_vjikafm48ed","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>As a wizard, you&rsquo;re an arcane scientist and, like any scientist, you could be diligent, eccentric, or even stark-raving mad. Among the other magically inclined, you have every reason to be proud of your talents. Bards? Stage magicians obsessed with fame. Sorcerers? Freaks who won the genetic lottery. You earned your power. You&rsquo;re a bona fide genius and it&rsquo;s unlikely that anyone will soon forget how bright your brilliance burned, especially if you go out in a fireball of glory.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Arcana, Common Knowledge, Cosmology, Language, Lore, Science, Spellcasting</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges:</strong> Arcane Background (Magic), Arcane Resistance, Improved Arcane Resistance, Linguist, University Trained</p>\n<p><strong>Power Edges:</strong> Channeling, Concentration, Power Surge, Wizard</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Familiar, Scholar</p>","_id":"XAE3YbGvQQp3seS3"}
{"name":"Dol Arrah","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_t6c26zc4ga","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/5. Faiths of Khorvaire#/CF_SEP/5.1. Sovereign Host","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Dol Arrah</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<h3>God of Honor and Sacrifice</h3>\n<p><img class=\"right table-figure\" src=\"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/art/symbols/dol-arrah.webp\" alt=\"Dol Arrah's Symbol\" width=\"357\" height=\"400\" /></p>\n<p>Dol Arrah is the light, not only of the sun, but of the best aspects of the mortal soul. She is the god of honor, forthrightness, and self-sacrifice. Many Vassals see her as no less vital to civilization than @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Aureon]{Aureon} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Boldrei]{Boldrei}, and they believe that when the mortal races accept this truth, the world will become much brighter. Dol Arrah is the deity of honorable combat, self-sacrifice, and sunlight, manifests as a peacemaker, a careful planner, and a strategist.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Dol Arrah is the sun that drives away the darkness. She stands for wisdom in war and for those who fight with honor, pursue justice, and make sacrifices for the greater good. She is the patron of paladins, diplomats, all who seek justice, and warriors who fight with wisdom and honor as much as with weapons.&nbsp; To a lesser extent, she is also the patron of explorers, who bring the light of knowledge to dark places, and to all who revere the sun. She aids @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Arawai]{Arawai} by lighting her way during the growing season.</p>\n<p>In addition, in her role as a sun god, she brings light to pierce the darkest places of the world. She is commonly represented as a human or half-elf knight shining with holy radiance, and sometimes as a red dragon perched on a cloud. She is said to be the sister of @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Arawai]{Dol Dorn} and the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Arawai]{Mockery}.&nbsp;</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Portfolio:</strong> Honor, sacrifice, light, the sun, diplomacy.</li>\n<li><strong>Symbol:</strong> A rising sun, a red dragon, or the Octogram in bright yellow-gold and white, representing light and purity.</li>\n<li><strong>Favored Weapon:</strong> Halberd</li>\n<li><strong>Priest Training:</strong> Dol Arrah&rsquo;s priests must have the highest integrity. Many were warriors, diplomats, or law officers before becoming priests. In all cases, they are people of sterling reputation.</li>\n<li><strong>Quests:</strong> Dol Arrah&rsquo;s priests quest to bring peace to warring factions, to expose deceptions, to aid soldiers fighting for justice, and to defend the helpless against invaders.</li>\n<li><strong>Prayers and Rites:</strong> Dol Arrah does not require specific items for sacrifice, so long as they have true meaning to the petitioner.</li>\n<li><strong>Shrines:</strong> Dol Arrah&rsquo;s shrines have large east-facing windows, to let in the light of the dawn. They are normally stone and are easily defensible, though not as fortresslike as those of her brother @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Arawai]{Dol Dorn}.</li>\n<li><strong>Signature Power:</strong>&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{Light} (not darkness)</em></li>\n<li><strong>Available Powers:</strong>\n<div class=\"available-powers\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Analyze Foe]{Analyze Foe}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]{Arcane Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{Banish}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]{Blind}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]{Bolt}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost/Lower Trait} (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Attributes} only)</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burst]{Burst}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Champion of Faith]{Champion of Faith}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Consecrate Ground]{Consecrate Ground}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]{Confusion}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Damage Field]{Damage Field}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]{Darksight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{Deflection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Divination]{Divination}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{Elemental Manipulation} (air or fire only)</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Environmental Protection]{Environmental Protection} (fire/heat only)</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.False Health]{False Health}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]{Farsight}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fear]{Fear}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Gift of Battle]{Gift of Battle}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{Havoc}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Holy Symbol]{Holy Symbol}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Jet]{Jet}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Leaping]{Leaping}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{Protection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{Relief}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Ressurection]{Ressurection}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sentry]{Sentry}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{Speed} (not sloth)</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{Smite}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Speak Language]{Speak Language}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]{Stun}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Elemental]{Summon Elemental} (fire only)</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{Telekinesis}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wall Walker]{Wall Walker}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Ward]{Ward}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Warrior's Gift]{Warrior's Gift}</p>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Trappings: </strong>Clergy and followers must have a light, heat, or fire trapping whenever possible. They cannot take cold, darkness or necromantic trappings.</li>\n<li><strong>Transgressions:</strong> Disciples who violate their core beliefs suffer will suffer a crisis of faith, disconnecting them from the source of their power. Minor sins give the disciple &ndash;2 to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Faith]{Faith} for a week. Major sins rob him of all arcane powers for a week. Mortal sins cause the disciple to break from their faith until the penitent hero completes from great quest or task of atonement to regain his lost powers (DM's call).</li>\n</ul>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Transgressions</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Severity</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Example</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Minor</td>\n<td>Lying, refusing aid to those in need, not welcoming the sun each morning, performing a minor evil or immoral act</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Major</td>\n<td>Theft, turning away those in dire need, refusing to fight the forces of darkness, commiting a major evil or immoral act, not standing up against immoral behavior</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mortal</td>\n<td>Harming an innocent, denying a sacrifice for the greater good, willfully aiding the forces of darkness</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<br />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"modules/swade-core-rules/assets/icons/savageworlds-logo.png","_id":"XDcEQDpEpPYzSslc"}
{"name":"Hinder or Hurry","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_53szy0z05dw","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. Magic#/CF_SEP/4.3. Power Modifiers","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<h3>Hinder or Hurry</h3>\n<p>By taking an additional &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} the power can be modified to either hinder or help a targets ability to move.</p>\n<p>The target is slowed in some way, perhaps due to intense cold, a slippery surface, or even binding matter or energy. His base @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} is reduced by 2 until the power expires.</p>\n<p>A caster can Hurry the recipient instead. He might get increased energy, sure footing, or more powerful muscles. His @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace}&nbsp; is increased by 2.</p>\n<p>Effects of either modifier aren&rsquo;t cumulative.</p>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","_id":"Y9iVOIf1rH5LerbN"}
{"name":"Using Magic","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_3t20aa8en26","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. Magic#/CF_SEP/4.1. Using Magic","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Using Magic</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<aside class=\"half-torn-parchment floated-aside\">\n<h2>A Changed System</h2>\n<p>Fans of the <cite>Savage Worlds</cite> rules will recognize many terms. However, this magic system is not the same as in the Savage Worlds core rules, having been heavily modified to fit the style of magic present the <cite>Eberron Campaign Setting</cite>.</p>\n<p>A brief summary of the major changes is listed below.</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li>No Power Points are used. Instead, spells suffer a Casting Modifier, which can be \"worked off\" by taking longer to cast the spell. While mages can therefore cast more frequently, magic can be slower to invoke.</li>\n<li>There are multiple Arcane Backgrounds that have been added and the core Arcane Backgrounds have been modified. Use the rules provided as part as this system for each background.</li>\n<li>There are different effects for Dynamic Backlash for each type of magic. This replaces the one size fits all optional Dynamic Backlash rule for magical backlash.</li>\n<li>New spells have been added, specifically ones that are used in the <cite>Eberron Campaign Setting</cite>. It is recommended that you take a look at these.</li>\n<li>Some spells have been modified from the core rules. Use these versions instead.</li>\n<li>Spells have a much longer Duration than in the <cite>Savage Worlds</cite> core rules, but cannot be maintained beyond the base Duration.</li>\n<li>Rules for ritual magic are included to allow creation of powerful spells at the cost of time and coin.</li>\n</ul>\n</aside>\n<p>The following setting rules apply to&nbsp;<em>all</em> forms of Arcane Backgrounds in the <cite> Savage Eberron</cite> setting. Unless a change is noted below, the normal rules apply.</p>\n<h3>Using Magic</h3>\n<p>As an action, a hero activates a power by picking a target within Range and making an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll minus the Casting Modifier.</p>\n<p>Success means the power activates as usual. A raise grants any additional bonuses stated in its description.</p>\n<p>Failure means the caster is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} and the power does not activate. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} when activating a power is called Backlash. The player immediately rolls on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Dynamic Backlash] table (or the Backlash table appropiate for their Arcane Background) and all currently active powers instantly terminate.</p>\n<p>Some of the Casting Modifiers are very high, making it seem all but very difficult to succeed for powerful magic. Magic is wide and far reaching in the world of Eberron, but powerful magic is very rare and only a few individuals know how to master such complex magic.</p>\n<p><strong>Spell Preparation:</strong> Each round a mage spends (after the first) preparing his spell reduces the Casting Modifier penalty by 1, to a minimum of zero. The caster may take no other actions during the round, including movement, though he retains his usual @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry] score if attacked. Once the caster finishes preparing, he must cast his spell on the following round or the magic is wasted and he must begin again.</p>\n<p>Other penalties to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} rolls aren't Casting Modifiers and cannot be reduced by spending extra time in preparation.</p>\n<p><strong>Canceling Spells:</strong> Casters can cancel their spells before the Duration expires. This is a free action and <em>immediately</em> cancels the effects of the spell.</p>\n<p><strong>Maintaining Spells:</strong> Characters can maintain those spells that allow it as long as desired, but each one maintained inflicts a &minus;1 to all further @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} rolls.</p>\n<h3>Components</h3>\n<p>Manipulating magic in Eberron requires components to work properly. A wizard begins the game with 10 components. Each casting uses one set of ingredients per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} of the spell. Additional components cost 1 galifar (gp) each.</p>\n<p>A wizard who doesn't have sufficient components to cast a particular spell suffers a &minus;1 penalty to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll per missing component. Thus, if a mage wants to cast a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Veteran} spell (requiring 3 components) but only has a single component, he suffers a &minus;2 penalty.</p>\n<p>This is fixed and cannot be offset by spending additional time in preparation. Components are expended in the casting whether the roll is successful or not. Components are different based on arcane background, consult the background for some general ideas of what those might include.</p>\n<p><strong>Rare Components:</strong> By using more expensive, unique, and rare components the Casting Modifier can be reduced. The caster must replace all the necessary components to gain the benefit and as usual, the components are used up regardless of the ritual&rsquo;s outcome. At a cost of 25 galifars (gp) for each component, the caster ignores a &minus;1 penalty or for 100 galifars (gp) per component, he ignores a &minus;2 penalty.</p>\n<h3>Disruption</h3>\n<p>Disruption can happen one of two ways.</p>\n<p><strong>During Casting Preparation:</strong> A mage must maintain concentration while casting. If he takes any damage during this time, the magic may be disrupted. To maintain concentration, the caster must succeed on an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill}. The roll is made after any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak rolls} If he wins, he may continue casting. If he fails, his casting is ruined, components spent, and he must begin again.</p>\n<p>A caster who is Shaken by non-damaging means, such as a Test of Wills, must make a simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} to maintain concentration.</p>\n<p><strong>Active Spells: </strong>A caster who has an active spell in play (one with a Duration listed as a time increment) may be disrupted if he takes damage. This works as above, except if the mage fails his roll all of his active spells are dropped after the attack that caused the disruption. With success, he keeps all his active spells functioning.</p>\n<p>A caster with active spells who is injured while casting another spell makes just a single roll. On a failure, he loses all his active spells and must start his current casting from scratch.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Articles on the Use of Magic</h2>\n<div class=\"swade-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Arcane Backgrounds}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Powers Modifiers}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Powers Summary List]{Powers Summary list}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Rituals]{Rituals}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","_id":"aJroj0nks5dMw2qn"}
{"name":"Barbarian","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.OwFGvHEjm9cHtgDD"},"cf":{"id":"temp_vjikafm48ed","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Even in these enlightened times, primal warriors linger on the edges of Khorvaire. Fearsome fighters, defined by durability, speed, instinct, and the ability to channel oneself into a physical frenzy. Traditionally barbarians are savage champions of cultures seen as primitive, relying on force and fury in place of sophisticated techniques.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Athletics, Fighting, Intimidation, Notice, Riding, Stealth, Survival</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Alertness, Berserk, True Berserker, Brawny, Brute</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Any combat edge</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Monster Hunter</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Humiliate, Provoke, Strong Willed, Iron Will</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Danger Sense, Liquid Courage</p>","_id":"aOQbfzWZeA0eiWMN"}
{"name":"Swashbuckler","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.Wl3UstbQHWHgaplR"},"cf":{"id":"temp_vjikafm48ed","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>You focus your training on the art of the blade, relying on speed, elegance, and charm in equal parts. While some warriors are brutes clad in heavy armor, your method of fighting looks almost like a performance. Duelists and pirates typically belong to this archetype. A Swashbuckler excels in single combat, and can fight with two weapons while safely darting away from an opponent.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Athletics, Fighting, Intimidate, Notice, Performance, Persuasion, Stealth, Taunt</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Ambidextrous, Elan, Fleet-Footed, Quick</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Block, Improved Block, Close Fighting, Improved Close Fighting, Dirty Fighter, Really Dirty Fighter, Dodge, Improved Dodge, Extraction, Improved Extraction, Feint, First Strike, Improved First Strike, Level Headed, Improved Level Headed, Lunge, Two-Fisted</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Acrobat, Combat Acrobat, Femme Fatale/Ladykiller, Thief</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Humiliate, Menacing</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Something</p>","_id":"bmVGcgErU33NpcPe"}
