{"name":"Human","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.p3IjYDRfpFs5fvXk"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7967rzk60vt","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Human</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>The first human settlers came to Khorvaire about 3,000 years ago, landing in the area now known as the Lhazaar Principalities. From there, they began a slow but inexorable spread across the continent, disrupting the placid elven empire ofAerenal and leaving further ruined remnants of fallen Dhakaani goblin kingdoms in their wake. During this migration, they founded the settlements that would grow into the Five Nations. Even today humans make up the majority of the population in these countries. Despite their relatively short lifespans&mdash;or perhaps because of them&mdash;humans are innovative, adaptable, and aggressive, always pushing their limits and pursuing new ideas.</p>\n<p>Humans prove extremely diverse; a barbarian from the Demon Wastes has little in common with a Brelish rogue. When creating a human character, consider where you're from and how that's reflected in your class and background. Chapter 2 presents an overview of the nations of Khorvaire and ideas for characters tied to those lands. Aundair is a logical place of origin for a wizard character, but your wizard could be a down-andout arcanist from the alleys of Sham or a Lhazaar pirate with a knack for the mystic arts.</p>\n<p>If you want to jump-start your ideas for a human character's origins, you can roll on the Human Origins table.</p>\n<h3>Humans and Dragonmarks</h3>\n<p>Five different dragonmarks appear among humans, reflecting their dominant status among the races of Khorvaire:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The <em>Mark of Making </em>is found in House Cannith, which has used it to become one of the most powerful houses, creating an abundance of both magical and technological wonders.</li>\n<li>The <em>Mark of Passage </em>aids the humans of House Orien in operating the lightning rail and trade caravans running across the continent.</li>\n<li>The <em>Mark of Sentinel </em>makes the bodyguards, mercenaries, and Sentinel Marshals of House Deneith widely respected across Khorvaire.</li>\n<li>The <em>Mark of Handling </em>appears in House Vadalis, which uses it to breed fine mounts and other creatures.</li>\n<li>Humans also number among House Tharashk and manifest the <em>Mark of Finding</em> with their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Half-orc]{half-orc} and @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{orc} kin.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Adaptable: </strong>umans are extremely easy to adapt and learn new things. They begin play with one free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Novice} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edge}. They must meet all the requirements for the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edge} as usual.</li>\n<li><strong>Skilled:</strong> Humans are innovative and adapable. They start with a d4 in any two skills based on their experiences, education, training, or culture. If the chosen skill is a core skill, skill), it starts at d6 and the skill&rsquo;s maximum increases to d12+1.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/art/races/human.webp\" alt=\"Human inquisitive at work\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-rules/assets/art/human.webp","_id":"pMnKtz1ySCDIPHms"}
{"name":"Arcane Background (Druid)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_e33lugmfz55","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. Magic#/CF_SEP/4.2. Arcane Backgrounds","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<h2>Arcane Background (Druid)</h2>\n<div>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Edge:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Druid)]</li>\n<li><strong>Requirements:</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Novice}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} d8+, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Druidism] d4+</li>\n<li><strong>Arcane Skill: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Druidism] (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit})</li>\n<li><strong>Connected to Eberron:</strong>&nbsp;Druids may take Edges that require Arcane Background (Miracles).</li>\n<li><strong>Powers of Nature:&nbsp;</strong>Druids are powerful in the wilds, but suffer within artifical or worked structures.</li>\n<li><strong>Backlash:&nbsp;</strong>When a druid rolls a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} on a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Druidism] roll, the Dungeon Master rolls on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Dynamic Backlash] table to see what happens.</li>\n<li><strong>Starting Powers: </strong>2</li>\n<li><strong>Available Powers:</strong>\n<div class=\"available-powers\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Accelerate Healing]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Analyze Foe]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Animate War Tree]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Arcane Protection]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Augury]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Becalm]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blind]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bolt]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Bridge]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Burrow]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Confusion]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Consecrate Ground]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Curse]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Darksight]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Disguise]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Divination]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Form]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Empathy] (animals only)</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Environmental Protection]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Farsight]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fear]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Feast]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Fly]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Growth/Shrink]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Holy Symbol]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibilty]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Jet]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Leaping]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Message] (animals only)</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Link] (animals only)</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Rider] (animals only)</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sentry]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Shape Change]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Slumber]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Stun]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Beast]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Summon Elemental]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Tempest]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Wall Walker]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Ward]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Whirlwind]</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Zephyr]</p>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Playing a Druid</h2>\n<p>Druids draw primal magic from the world itself. The process isn&rsquo;t like the spells of a wizard or the tools of an artificer, nor is it a divine petition to a higher power. Well, not exactly. Legend recounts how the great progenitor dragon Eberron enveloped the jealous evil of Khyber in the living prison that would become the world. If arcane magic comes from the tears of Siberys above, then Druidic magic is the blood and breath of Eberron herself, granting power to those who seek to defend her and the natural order from the threats beyond.</p>\n<p>Most druids are swathed in tradition, usually initiated by a sect that teaches the secrets of this primal magic while also charging the aspirant with specific duties. While some sects are loosely aligned, each one has its own ideas as to the role their kind should play in the world.</p>\n<p>Most druids come from the Eldeen Reaches, where their animistic religion is the dominant faith. Others are found anywhere that nature&rsquo;s spirit is strong, from the craggy mountains that house the Mror Holds to the fetid swamps of the Shadow Marches. Some druids from the Eldeen Reaches espouse radical philosophies that oppose the use of &ldquo;unnatural&rdquo; magic and condemn the building of settlements. Most druids are more moderate in their beliefs about the proper balance of nature, magic, and civilization.</p>\n<h3>Druids and Civilization</h3>\n<p>Most druids come from the Eldeen Reaches, where their animistic religion is the dominant faith. Others are found anywhere that nature&rsquo;s spirit is strong, from the craggy mountains that house the Mror Holds to the fetid swamps of the Shadow Marches. Some druids from the Eldeen Reaches espouse radical philosophies that oppose the use of &ldquo;unnatural&rdquo; magic and condemn the building of settlements. Most druids are more moderate in their beliefs about the proper balance of nature, magic, and civilization.</p>\n<p>You can roll on the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-tables.Druidic Beliefs] table to see how your druid views civilization.</p>\n<h3>Druids and Sovereign Host</h3>\n<p>Traditionally, the Sovereign Host is a civilized faith with shrines in the great cities of the Five Nations but a number of shrines to deities tied to nature can be found in the wilds. Balinor is the Sovereign of the Hunt, Arawai brings nature&rsquo;s bounty, and the Devourer embodies its destructive power and the hunger that reclaims its waste. In Eberron, a priest of Balinor isn&rsquo;t inherently required to follow one trail or the other, but the main differences between the two lay in how command of nature is granted, and the purpose for which they use it. While it&rsquo;s common for the two paths to recognize one another, such respect isn&rsquo;t always equal.</p>\n<p>From a philosophical perspective, a druid is an envoy of nature with a connection to the environment itself, not a servant of a higher power. By contrast, the cleric serves a higher power and holds dominion over the natural world. While druids shun such metal armaments, nature clerics usually practice combat in manmade heavy metal armors until proficient. Yet, clerics lack the primal understanding required to communicate in Druidic and to assume Wild Shape, which is a reflection of the druid&rsquo;s deep connection to the natural world.</p>\n<p>Such differences lead to a deep disconnect between the typical druid and a nature worshiping cleric. The Warden of the Wood might see the priests of Balinor as an arrogant outsider, a city-dweller who believes that humanoids hold some sort of divine right over the planet, which is admittedly often the case. To the priestess of Arawai, nature is something that serves the people and her primary concern is ensuring a bountiful harvest, not driving farmers from their fields.</p>\n<p>While this is the obvious contrast, it&rsquo;s possible to create a character who uses one class while following the opposite path. Perhaps you want to play a priest of Balinor but you love the idea of hunting in the form of a wolf, or you want to be Ashbound but have no interest in ever assuming a Wild Shape. While there will be the occasional disconnect, like the Ashbound cleric can&rsquo;t use Wild Shape, the Balinor druid can&rsquo;t turn undead, look to juxtapose these ideas to best match the story and experience you&rsquo;re looking for, using backgrounds like the acolyte or outlander to cultivate the option.</p>\n<h2>Casting</h2>\n<p>Regardless of how they view civilization, druids are more powerful in the wilds, but have more difficultly controling the elemental energies within more civilized locations. Druids must make gestures with at least one free hand and speak aloud various magical words at least at a whisper. If either their hands are bound or they are prevented from speaking, they cannot cast their spells.</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Druid Casting Modifiers</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Casting Modifier</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Enviroment</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>+1</td>\n<td>In the wild or natural caverns</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>+0</td>\n<td>Rural (farm, worked cavern, mine)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&minus;1</td>\n<td>Urban (town or city, artificial structures)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<br />\n<h2>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trappings}</h2>\n<p>Druids interact constantly with nature, drawing all their power from it. They regularly perform various rituals while they rest or pray. They regularly tend to the natural order of things. This opens their conduits of power to the natural energies and allows them to activate powers later without begining the appeal in the moment.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Druidic powers are cast through chants, talismans, and talking with nature itself. Depending on the spell, the druid may cast bones, sprinkle of ash, rubbing a talisman, beseeching the forces of nature. Trappings for the spells of druids should all include natural components or aspects.</p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","_id":"q3hdsgwk5MnF9Eby"}
{"name":"Fighter/Warrior","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.BLSS2IDTA3BoVZPB"},"cf":{"id":"temp_vjikafm48ed","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Soldiers, mercenaries, bodyguards&ndash;these are just a few of the roles played by the guilds of House Deneith. The Blademarks Guild, the Defenders Guild, and the Sentinel Marshals train the best of Khorvaire&rsquo;s fighters and warriors. Others unaffiliated with these guilds find their way in post-war Khorvaire, some formerly soldiers fighting on behalf of their nation currently seeking independent employment or joining local law enforcement.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills: </strong>Athletics, Fighting, Gabling, Intimidation, Shooting</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges: </strong>Ambidextrous, Brave, Brawny, Brute</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Any combat edge</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Guardian, Soldier</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Menacing, Provoke</p>","_id":"qIiiMLFp1EWvvr3w"}
{"name":"Shadowing","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_v2dfoof50lp","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/3. Setting Rules","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Shadowing</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>On occasion, a hero may wish to follow another character&mdash;a \"mark\"&mdash;without being noticed, such as following a cultist back to a hidden temple or trailing a wealthy noble. This is not the same as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chase}&mdash;though it might lead to one if the person being followed discovers he has unwanted attention.</p>\n<p>Shadowing is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} between the Shadower's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth] skill @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by his opponent's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice] roll. If the character is shadowing by other means of conveyance than walking, he uses the lower of his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth] or the appropriate \"maneuvering\" skill (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding], @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting], etc.).</p>\n<p>Should the shadower roll at least a 4 and win the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} he manages to follow unnoticed. If his roll wins the contest but is less than a 4, the character loses his mark but isn't seen. If the hero loses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} with a 4 or better, his target is followed but detects him. If he loses both the contest and fails to score at least a 4 on his roll, then not only does he fail to keep shadowing, but his target gets a good look at him. If the shadower is discovered, he can continue to follow his mark, but it becomes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} of his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice] versus his opponent's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth] (or maneuvering Trait if lower) to not lose the target.</p>\n<p>While in an urban enviroment, each roll covers roughly fifteen minutes of time, so it's possible several rolls may be required.</p>\n<p>Finally, it's very hard to shadow a target who moves faster than the follower. If the opponent has a higher base @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace}, the shadower suffers &minus;2 to his Trait roll. If the mark's normal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} is more than 50% higher than the follower (round up), the penalty is &minus;4.</p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","_id":"qYR2BEsPKkKbHrKp"}
{"name":"Merchant","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.jxNfRTYaBJROlyxo"},"cf":{"id":"temp_vjikafm48ed","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.2. Character Concepts","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<p>Merchants earn their living by buying and selling the works of others. Perhaps working for a dragonmarked house, an independent business, or just for yourself. They help establish company trade routes, negotiate prices, and ensure goods head where they’re needed.</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> Common Knowledge, Notice, Persuasion</p>\n<p><strong>Hindrance:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Background Edges:</strong> Charismatic</p>\n<p><strong>Combat Edges:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Leadership Edges:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Power Edges:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Professional Edges:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Social Edges:</strong> Something</p>\n<p><strong>Weird Edges:</strong> Scavenger</p>","_id":"rnahacQ4wRnGvOoW"}
{"name":"Tiefling","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.9HqI82YeMZdTAeIK"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7967rzk60vt","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Tiefling</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Many tieflings are born to the Carrion Tribes, the barbarians who live in the Demon Wastes. Such tieflings are touched by the fiendish forces bound beneath the Wastes, and the tribes consider them to be blessed. If you're playing such a tiefling, why have you left the Wastes? It could be that you were destined for some evil purpose-perhaps even serving as an avatar for an imprisoned Overlord-and you are fleeing that destiny.</p>\n<p>Other tieflings are shaped not by fiendish powers, but by the influence of the fiend-tainted planes. Such tieflings might be born in manifest zones, where a plane exerts influence over a region. Planar tieflings are oddities, often seen as strange but not necessarily evil.</p>\n<p>Finally, the Venomous Demesne&mdash;a city-state hidden on the far side of Droaam&mdash;is populated by tieflings. These tieflings descend from Sarlonan mages who bargained with dark powers, with the Demesne's lords being powerful warlocks and wizards. The Venomous Demesne has had no significant contact with the Five Nations and few know it exists. Your character could be an envoy or exile from it, or simply an adventurer driven by a desire to see what lies beyond your homeland.</p>\n<h3>Self-Reliant and Suspicious</h3>\n<p>Tieflings rarely appear in the cities and towns of Khorvaire, with most dwelling at the fringes of civilization. Tieflings subsist in small minorities found mostly in human cities or towns, often in the roughest quarters of those places, where they grow up to be swindlers, thieves, or crime lords. Sometimes they live among other minority populations in enclaves where they are treated with more respect.</p>\n<p>Lacking a homeland, tieflings know that they have to make their own way in the world and that they have to be strong to survive. They are not quick to trust anyone who claims to be a friend, but when a tiefling&rsquo;s companions demonstrate that they trust him or her, the tiefling learns to extend the same trust to them. And once a tiefling gives someone loyalty, the tiefling is a firm friend or ally for life.</p>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Fiedish Sorcery: </strong>Tieflings inherently have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Background (Gifted)]{Arcane Background (Gifted)} and they may start with one power of their choice. They also have a d4 in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Focus]{Focus} (Spirit).</li>\n<li><strong>Inferal Resistance: </strong>Due to Teiflings infernal heritage they recieve a +4 bonus to resist @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heat]{heat} and fire effects. Damage from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heat]{heat}&nbsp;and fire is also reduced by 4.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Language]{Language}:</strong> Tieflings start with a d8 in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Infernal}.</li>\n<li><strong>Low Light Vision: </strong>Tieflings infernal heritage allows them to see into the darkness of Khyber. ignore penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim or Dark illumination} (but not Pitch Darkness).</li>\n<li><strong>Outsider (Major):</strong> Tieflings are viewed with heavy suspicious in most areas of civilizied culture. Tieflings have a -2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls made to influence those who aren't their kind. They also have very few is any legal rights in most civilized nations.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/art/races/tiefling.webp\" alt=\"Tiefling mage casting a spell\" /></div>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-rules/assets/art/tiefling.webp","_id":"sg0Tau6fSkQI7AQT"}
{"name":"Bugbear","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.L4NqGfd9AVja33DY"},"cf":{"id":"temp_7967rzk60vt","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation#/CF_SEP/1.1. Races","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Bugbear</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>The goblinoid species&mdash;goblins, hobgoblins, and bugbears&mdash;were once the dominant civilization in Khorvaire, with the goblinoid Empire of Dhakaan ruling the continent for thousands ofyears. It was crippled by a long conflict with the daelkyr and their aberrant armies; even though the daelkyr were defeated, the seeds of madness took root in the empire and tore it apart. Today there are four primary goblinoid cultures in Khorvaire.</p>\n<p>Known as <em>guul'dar</em>, or \"strong people\", among the <em>dar</em> or goblin races. <em>Guul'dar</em> are born for battle and mayhem being fierce and aggressive. Surviving by raiding and hunting, they bully the weak and despite being bossed around. In Darguun they living in tribes in the Marguul mountains, or in the <em>ghaal'dur </em>tribes ruling Darguun often serving as shock troops being ruled by the hobgoblins with superior numbers and intellect.</p>\n<h3>The Marguul</h3>\n<p>The Marguul bugbears threw off the yoke of the <em>ghaal'dar</em> long ago, seizing territory in the Seawall Mountains in the south of Darguun. They are infamous raiders, and while they have brokered a truce with the Ghaal'dar, anyone venturing into the Seawall Mountains had best travel with a Marguul guide.</p>\n<p>As a Marguul bugbear, you are savage and proud of it. The Marguul worship the Mockery and believe in victory by any means necessary: there is no such thing as honor on the battlefield. It's certainly an unusual choice for a player character, but if you've taken a liking to a particular group of the small folk, you could be a powerful ally.</p>\n<h3>The Heirs of Dhakaan</h3>\n<p>Though the Dhakaani Empire defeated the alien daelkyr, the war left seeds ofcorruption strewn throughout the empire. As Dhakaan began to fall, a number of generals and governors gathered their forces and retreated into shelters deep within the earth, determined to preserve their civilization until the Empire could finally be restored. After thousands of years, their descendants have finally emerged, competing among themselves to determine which leader deserves the imperial crown. Once this is settled, they will turn to the conquest of Darguun and Khorvaire.</p>\n<p>The Dhakaani are far fewer in number than the <em>ghaal'dar</em>; they had to carefully limit their population in the underground vaults they've dwelled in for the past age. However, they have held onto the martial discipline and techniques that allowed their ancestors to dominate the continent. Their weaponsmiths are superior even to the artificers of House Cannith, and they are experts in the working of adamantine and other exotic metals. Anyone who presumes to look down upon goblinoids should be surprised by the skills of the Dhakaani.</p>\n<p>The Heirs of Dhakaan are an agnostic society and don't have clerics, paladins, or druids. Their focus is on martial excellence, and their spiritual leaders are bards, who tell tales of past glory. Among the Dhakaan, goblinoids work together. Hobgoblins are the strategists and commanders, typically having the skills of fighters, bards, or rangers. Bugbears cultivate a focused battle rage and are typically barbarians. Goblins are largely artisans and laborers, but exceptional goblins join the khesh'dar (\"silent folk\"), learning the skills of rogues, monks, or rangers. The khesh'dar spread agents across the Five Nations, and one can never know when a city goblin might turn out to be an assassin.</p>\n<p>As an adventurer from a Dhakaani clan, consider why are you working with the other player characters? Are you a scout gathering information? Are you searching for allies to defeat a rival clan, or to support your own unlikely bid for the Imperial throne? Are you an exile? If so, do you hope to regain your position, or have you abandoned your ties to the Dhakaani?</p>\n<h2>Racial Abilities</h2>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.Bloodthirsty]{Bloodthirsty}:</strong>&nbsp;Bugbears are very brutal killers and like to inflict pain.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Brute Strength:</strong> Bugbears are naturally strong, and start with a d6 in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of a d4. This increases their maximum @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} to d12+1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Language]{Language}:</strong> Bugbears start with a d8 in @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Languages]{Goblin}.</li>\n<li><strong>Large Size: </strong>Bugbears average about seven to eight feet tall, increasing their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (and therefore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}) by 1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Long-Limbs]{Long-Limbs}:</strong> Bugbears are long-limbed goblinoids. They have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} +1.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-racial-abilities.Low-Light Vision (Bugbear)]{Low-Light Vision}:</strong> Bugbear eyes are accustomed to the dark of Khyber. They ignore penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim or Dark illumination} (but not Pitch Darkness).</li>\n<li><strong>Silent Ambushers:</strong> Bugbears are natural ambushers. They start with a d6 in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth}. This increases their maximum @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} to a d12+1.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"center vert-spacer\"><img class=\"table-figure\" src=\"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/art/races/bugbear.webp\" alt=\"Bugbear warrior on the prowl.\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-rules/assets/art/bugbear.webp","_id":"swOEdUth0tfq0KK2"}
{"name":"Selective Targets","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_53szy0z05dw","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. Magic#/CF_SEP/4.3. Power Modifiers","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<h3>Selective Targets</h3>\n<p>With intense focus, the caster can choose not to affect any or all individual targets within a power's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{area of effect} (picking all enemies instead of allies in a <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Blast]{blast}</em>, for example) with a &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}.</p>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","_id":"t9Lb0IKevtrptI0D"}
{"name":"Edges","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_jtibz2gzdj","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/1. Character Creation","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{"references":{}}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div>\n<h1>Edges</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>Below is a list of Edges common to most settings. You&rsquo;ll find new Edges designed for your game world in official <em>Savage Worlds</em> books as well.</p>\n<p>The Edges are grouped by type to help during character creation. You&rsquo;ll find a summary below.</p>\n<p>Unless an Edge specifically says otherwise, it may only be selected once.</p>\n<p><strong>Forbidden Edges:</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Background (Weird Science)], @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Channeling], @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Double Tap]{Double Tap}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Extra Effort], @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Gadgeteer] @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Power Points], @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Power Surge], @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Rapid Fire], @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Rapid Recharge], @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Rock and Roll!], @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Soul Drain], @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Two-Gun Kid] and any Edges which list these as a requirement.</p>\n<p><strong>Altered Edges:</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Background (Miracles)], @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Aristocrat], All core Arcane Backgrounds,</p>\n<p>Holy Warrior undergoes a few changes and can only be chosen by priests. Champion is only available to paladins.</p>\n<p><strong class=\"red-text\">Requirements:</strong>&nbsp;Below each Edge is the minimum Rank (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Advancement}) required to take it along with any other prerequisites such as attributes, skills, or other Edges.</p>\n</div>\n<figure class=\"figure table-figure\">\n<figcaption class=\"figure-heading\">Edge Summaries</figcaption>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Arcane Background Edges</h2>\n<h3>(\"AB\" is Arcane Background)</h3>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Aberrant Dragonmark)]</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>AB for outcasts that manifest an Aberrant Dragonmark.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Dragonmark)]</td>\n<td>N, DGMK Race</td>\n<td>AB for a member of any of the Dragomarked Houses.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Druidism)]</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>AB for the Druids of the Shadow Marches, Eldeen Reaches or other areas.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Background (Gifted)]</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>AB for heroes that have inate magical abilities that have no other classification.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Herbal Alchemy)]</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>AB for thost that create potions, poultices, ointments, edibles and other alchemical products.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Magecraft)]</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>AB for magewrights and artificers to harness magic for technology.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Background (Magic)]</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>AB for wizards that study and manipulate the fabric of magic.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Background (Miracles)]</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>Ab for the faithful who follow one of the relgions of Eberron.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Background (Psionics)]</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>AB for those that use their own mental energy to manipulate matter and people. Most common in Sarlona.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Song Magic)]</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>AB for Bards, Skalds, and Troubadours.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Background (Wand Magic)]</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>AB for Wandslingers who use wands, staves and rods to cast spells.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Background Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Alertness]{Alertness}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} Rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Ambidextrous]{Ambidextrous}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>Ignore &ndash;2 penalty when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} rolls with off-hand.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Arcane skills targeting the hero suffer a &minus;2 penalty (even if cast by allies!); magical damage is reduced by 2.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Arcane Resistance]{Improved Arcane Resistance}</td>\n<td>N, Arcane Resistance</td>\n<td>As Arcane Resistance except penalty is increased to &minus;4 and magical damage is reduced by 4.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Aristocrat]</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} with upper class.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Attractive]{Attractive}</td>\n<td>N, V, d6</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Berserk]{Berserk}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>After being @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken or Wounded}, melee attacks must be@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Attack]{Wild Attacks}, +1 die type to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}, +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}, ignore one level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound penalties}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll hits random target. Take @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} after every five consecutive rounds, may choose to end rage with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll &ndash;2.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brave]{Brave}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d6</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks and &ndash;2 to rolls on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-macros.Fear Table]{Fear Table}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brawny]{Brawny}</td>\n<td>N, St d6, V d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (and therefore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}) +1. Treat @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Strength} as one die type higher for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Gear Notes]{Encumbrance} and Minimum Strength to use weapons, armor, or equipment.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brute]{Brute}</td>\n<td>N. St d6, V d6</td>\n<td>Link @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Agility} (including resistance). Short @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range} of any thrown item increased by +1. Double that for the adjusted Medium Range, and double again for Long Range.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Charismatic]{Charismatic}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Free reroll when using @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Elan]{Elan}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>+2 when spending a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to reroll a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Fame]{Fame}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>+1 Persuasion rolls when recognized (Common Knowledge), double usual fee for Performance.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Famous]{Famous}</td>\n<td>S, Fame</td>\n<td>+2&nbsp; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} when recognized, 5&times; or more usual fee for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Fast Healer]{Fast Healer}</td>\n<td>N, Vd8</td>\n<td>+2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Vigor} when rolling for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{natural healing}; check every 3 days.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Fleet-Footed]{Fleet-Footed}</td>\n<td>N, A d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} +2, increase running die one step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.House Scion]</td>\n<td>N, DGMK Race</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} with your Dragonmarked House.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Natural Swimmer]</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>+2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} to swimming, +1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} when swimming, and can hold breath 50% longer.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Linguist]{Linguist}</td>\n<td>N, Sm d6</td>\n<td>Character has d6 in languages equal to half her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Smarts} die.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Luck]{Luck}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>+1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} at the start of each session.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Great Luck]{Great Luck}</td>\n<td>N, Luck</td>\n<td>+2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} at the start of each session.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Quick]{Quick}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>The hero may discard and redraw @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Cards} of 5 or lower.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Rich]{Rich}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>Character starts with three times the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{starting funds} and a $150K annual salary.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Filthy Rich]{Filthy Rich}</td>\n<td>N, Rich</td>\n<td>Five times @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{starting funds} and $500K average salary.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.University Trained]</td>\n<td>N, Sm d8</td>\n<td>3 points for Knowledge skills, +1 point for use in a language.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Combat Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bilge Rat]</td>\n<td>N, A d8, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>No penalty for fighting in small or close quarters, unless it is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach] weapon.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Bilge Rat]</td>\n<td>S, Bilge Rat</td>\n<td>No penalty for using any weapon in small or close quarters.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Block]{Block}</td>\n<td>S, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>+1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Parry}, ignore 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Ganging Up]{Gang Up} bonus.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Block]{Improved Block}</td>\n<td>V, Block</td>\n<td>+2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Parry}, ignore 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Ganging Up]{Gang Up} bonus.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bodyguard]</td>\n<td>H, A d8, Block, Notice d8</td>\n<td>Attacks against one adjacent ally are rolled against the heroes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry}, as long as they reamin adjacent.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brawler]{Brawler}</td>\n<td>N, St d8, V d8</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} +1, add d4 to damage from fists; or increase it a die type if combined with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Claws)]{Claws}, or similar abilities.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Bruiser]{Bruiser}</td>\n<td>S, Brawler</td>\n<td>Increase unarmed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} damage a die type and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} another +1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Brutal]</td>\n<td>N, WC</td>\n<td>+1 to damage for each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Calculating]{Calculating}</td>\n<td>N, St d8, V d8</td>\n<td>Ignore up to 2 points of penalties on one action with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card)} of Five or less.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Charge]</td>\n<td>S, V d8, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>At end of run action may make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Free Attacks]{free attack} with not @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{multi-action} penalty.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Close Fighting]</td>\n<td>N, A d8, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>The hero gains a bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} equal to the enemy's weapon @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} +1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Close Fighting]</td>\n<td>N, Close Fighting</td>\n<td>As Close Fighting, but also gaining a +1 bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} equal to enemy weapons @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach} +1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Combat Reflexes]{Combat Reflexes}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>+2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} to recover from being @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Counterattack]{Counterattack}</td>\n<td>S, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>Free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack against one foe per round who failed a&nbsp; roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Counterattack]{Improved Counterattack}</td>\n<td>V, Counterattack</td>\n<td>As Counterattack, but against three failed attacks per round.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Dead Shot]{Dead Shot}</td>\n<td>WC, N, Athletics or Shooting d8</td>\n<td>First successful@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (Thorwing) or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} roll, double damage from when dealt a Joker.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Dodge]{Dodge}</td>\n<td>S, A d8</td>\n<td>&minus;2 to be hit by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Attacks]{ranged attacks}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Dodge]{Improved Dodge}</td>\n<td>S, Dodge</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evasion} totals.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Double Tap]{Double Tap}</td>\n<td>S, Shooting d6</td>\n<td>+1 to hit and damage when firing no more than @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Rate of Fire]{RoF 1} per action.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Extraction]{Extraction}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>One adjacent foe doesn&rsquo;t get a free attack when you @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Withdrawing From Melee]{withdraw from close combat}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Extraction]{Improved Extraction}</td>\n<td>S, Extraction</td>\n<td>Three adjacent foes don&rsquo;t get free attacks when you @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Withdrawing From Melee]{withdraw from close combat.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fast Mount]</td>\n<td>N, A d8, Riding d6</td>\n<td>Mount and dismount as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Foe]</td>\n<td>S, Sm d8, Athletics, Fighting, or Shooting d8</td>\n<td>+1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} against certain foe, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage]{bonus damage} is a d8 rather than d6.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Feint]{Feint}</td>\n<td>N, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>You may choose to make foe resist with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts Instead of Agility} during a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Fighting Test}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.First Strike]{First Strike}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>Free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack once per round when foe moves within @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved First Strike]{Improved First Strike}</td>\n<td>H, First Strike</td>\n<td>Free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack against up to three foes when they move within @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fighting Withdrawl]</td>\n<td>V, A d8, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>The hero may run while use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Defend]{Defend} action.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Free Runner]{Free Runner}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>Ignore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Difficult Ground} and add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} in foot @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{chases} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (climbing).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Frenzy]{Frenzy}</td>\n<td>S, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>Roll a second @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} die with one melee attack per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Frenzy]{Improved Frenzy}</td>\n<td>V, Frenzy</td>\n<td>Roll a second @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} die with up to two melee attacks per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Giant Killer]{Giant Killer}</td>\n<td>V</td>\n<td>+1d6 damage vs. creatures three @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Sizes} larger or more.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Giant Killer]</td>\n<td>H, Giant Killer</td>\n<td>Ignore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{armor} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{size} of a creature three @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size and Scale} larger or more.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Ground Fighter]</td>\n<td>N, A or St d6</td>\n<td>No penalties when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone}. +1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} against a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone} opponent.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Hard To Kill]{Hard To Kill}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Ignore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound penalties} when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls to avoid @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Bleeding Out}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Harder To Kill]{Harder To Kill}</td>\n<td>V, Hard to Kill</td>\n<td>Roll a die if the character perishes. Even if he&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated}, he survives somehow.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improvisational Fighter]{Improvisational Fighter}</td>\n<td>S, Sm d6</td>\n<td>Ignore &ndash;2 penalty when attacking with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Improvised Weapons]{Improvised Weapons}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Iron Jaw]{Iron Jaw}</td>\n<td>N, V d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak Rolls} and&nbsp; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Vigor} rolls to avoid @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{Knockout Blows}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Killer Instinct]{Killer Instinct}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>The hero gets a free reroll in any opposed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} he initiates.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Level Headed]{Level Headed}</td>\n<td>S, Sm d8</td>\n<td>Draw an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} each round in combat and choose which one to use.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Level Headed]{Improved Level Headed}</td>\n<td>S, Level Headed</td>\n<td>Draw two additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Cards} each round in combat and choose which one to use.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Lunge]</td>\n<td>N, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>Gain +1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{reach} with the adventurer's weapon.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Marksman]{Marksman}</td>\n<td>S, Athletics or Shooting d8</td>\n<td>Ignore up to 2 points of penalties from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range},@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{Cover}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Called Shots]{Called Shots}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Speed]{Speed}; or add +1 to first @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (Throwing) or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} roll. Character may not move or fire greater than @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Rate of Fire]{RoF 1}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist}</td>\n<td>N, Fighting d6</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Fighting} +1, fists and feet count as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}, add d4 damage die to unarmed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attacks (or increase die a step if you already have it).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Martial Warrior]{Martial Warrior}</td>\n<td>S, Martial Artist</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unarmed Defender]{Unarmed Fighting} +2, increase damage die type a step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Mighty Blow]{Mighty Blow}</td>\n<td>WC, N, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>On first successful @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll, double damage when dealt a Joker.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mighty Shot]</td>\n<td>V, St d8, Shooting d10</td>\n<td>Character rolls @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}+d6 for damage with a bow.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Mounted Combatant]</td>\n<td>N, Riding d8</td>\n<td>Ignores two points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} penalties and may spend a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak roll} for mount. May also make @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} roll to increase pace of mount by 2\".</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Nerves of Steel]{Nerves of Steel}</td>\n<td>N, V d8</td>\n<td>Ignore one level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound Penalties} penalties.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Nerves of Steel]{Improved Nerves of Steel}</td>\n<td>N, Nerves of Steel</td>\n<td>Ignore up to two levels of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound Penalties} penalties.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.No Mercy]{No Mercy}</td>\n<td>S</td>\n<td>+2 damage when spending a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to reroll damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Oversized Weapon Master]</td>\n<td>V, St d10, Fighting d10, Size 0</td>\n<td>The character may use a two-handed weapon with one hand.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Rapid Fire]{Rapid Fire}</td>\n<td>S, Shooting d6</td>\n<td>Increase @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Rate of Fire]{RoF} by 1 for one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attack per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Rapid Fire]{Improved Rapid Fire}</td>\n<td>V, Rapid Fire</td>\n<td>Increase @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Rate of Fire]{RoF} by 1 for up to two @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attacks per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Rock and Roll!]{Rock and Roll!}</td>\n<td>S, Shooting d8</td>\n<td>Ignore the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Recoil]{Recoil} penalty when firing weapons with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Rate of Fire]{RoF} of 2 or more. Character may not move.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Steady Hands]{Steady Hands}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>Ignore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Unstable Platform]{Unstable Platform} penalty; reduce running penalty to &ndash;1.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Steal Away]</td>\n<td>S, A d8, Stealth d6</td>\n<td>The hero can make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} roll as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} to hide when withdrawing.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sucker Punch]</td>\n<td>S, A d6, Fighting d8,First Strike</td>\n<td>If the hero succeeds on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}, they recieve a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Free Attacks]{Free Attack}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Sweep]{Sweep}</td>\n<td>N, St d8, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll at &ndash;2 to hit all targets in weapon&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach}, no more than once per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Sweep]{Improved Sweep}</td>\n<td>V, Sweep</td>\n<td>As above, but ignore the &ndash;2 penalty.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Takedown Move]</td>\n<td>S, Wrestler</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Push]{Push} moves are opposed at a &ndash;2 (&ndash;4 on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Trademark Weapon]{Trademark Weapon}</td>\n<td>N, d8 in related skill</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (Throwing), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} total with a specific weapon; +1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Parry} while weapon is readied.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Trademark Weapon]{Improved Trademark Weapon}</td>\n<td>S, Trademark Weapon</td>\n<td>The attack and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Parry} bonus increases to +2.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.True Berserker]</td>\n<td>N, Sp d6,&nbsp;</td>\n<td>The adventurer can make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} to go @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Berserk]{Berserk} at any time.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.True Hero]</td>\n<td>H, WC, Iron Jaw</td>\n<td>When the hero would get @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{incapacitated}, they get a free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak roll}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Two-Fisted]{Two-Fisted}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>Make one extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} roll with a second melee weapon in the off-hand at no Multi-Action penalty.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wrestler]</td>\n<td>N, A or St d6, Fighting d6</td>\n<td>Make make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting] roll rather than @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Grappling]{Grappling}. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Grappling]{Crushing} damage is increased to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} + d4.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Disciple Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n<td>xxx</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Leadership Edges</h2>\n<h3>(Command Range is 5\" or 10 Yards)</h3>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.A Few Good Men]</td>\n<td>H, Inspire, Sm d8 , Battle d10</td>\n<td>In @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, add one more Token to force calculations.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Born in Battle]</td>\n<td>S, Sm d8, Battle d8, Command</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle} rolls, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls concerning military matters.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Command]{Command}</td>\n<td>N, Sm d6</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras'} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned} recovery rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Command Presence]{Command Presence}</td>\n<td>S, Command</td>\n<td>Increase Command Range to 10&Prime; (20 yards)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Coordinated Firepower]</td>\n<td>V, Command, Sm d6,Athletics or Shooting d8+</td>\n<td>The hero adds a flat +2 attack bonus for additional ranged attacks for those within command range. Additional bonus damage on raises.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Cry Havoc!]</td>\n<td>V, Fervor, Sp d8, Battle d10</td>\n<td>In @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, the character may declare a charge that will cause his enemy to lose one extra token.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Death before Dishonor]</td>\n<td>V, Hold the Line, Sp d8, Battle d8</td>\n<td>In @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, the hero gains +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} when rolling for Morale.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Drop!]</td>\n<td>S, Command, Notice d6</td>\n<td>Allows to hero to command allies to drop @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{prone} out of turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fanaticism]</td>\n<td>S, Fervor</td>\n<td>Those in Command Range gain +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks and subtract 2 from rolls on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Fear Table]{Fear Table}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Fervor]{Fervor}</td>\n<td>V, Sp d8, Command</td>\n<td>Extras in range add +1 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} damage rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.help Me!]</td>\n<td>S, Command</td>\n<td>When an enemy moves adjacent to the hero, the hero may call for help acting as if they were on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hold]{Hold}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Hold the Line!]{Hold the Line!}</td>\n<td>S, Sm d8, Command</td>\n<td>+1 to&nbsp; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras'} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} in Command Range.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Inspire]{Inspire}</td>\n<td>S, Command</td>\n<td>Once per turn, the hero may roll his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle} skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} one type of Trait roll, and apply it to everyone in Command Range.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Natural Leader]{Natural Leader}</td>\n<td>S, Sp d8, Command</td>\n<td>Leadership Edges now apply to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Siege Breaker]</td>\n<td>S, Command, Sm d8, Battle d8</td>\n<td>In @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, the hero can increase the Siege Bonus when conducting a siege with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Siege Mentality]</td>\n<td>S, Command, Sm d8, Battle d8</td>\n<td>In @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mass Battles]{Mass Battles}, the hero can increase the Siege Bonus when defending in a siege with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Battle]{Battle} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Tactician]{Tactician}</td>\n<td>S, Sm d8, Command, Battle d6</td>\n<td>Draw an extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} each turn that may be assigned to any allied @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} in Command Range.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Master Tactician]{Master Tactician}</td>\n<td>V, Tactician</td>\n<td>Draw and distribute two extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Cards} instead of one.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Power Edges</h2>\n<h3>(\"AB\" is Arcane Background)</h3>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Artificer]</td>\n<td>S, AB (Dragonmark of Making, Magecraft, Magic, or Miracles), Arcana d10+, arcane skill d8+</td>\n<td>The artificer has the ability to create minor artifacts.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Artificer]{Master Artificer}</td>\n<td>V, Artificer</td>\n<td>The artificer has the ability to create stronger artifacts.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Devices]</td>\n<td>S, AB (Dragonmark of Making, Magecraft, Magic, or Miracles), Arcana d8, arcane skill d8</td>\n<td>Allows user to create arcane devices to share with others imbued with a single power.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Attune Arcane Weapon]</td>\n<td>S, Artificer</td>\n<td>The artificer gains +1 bonus to attack and damage with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Devices]{Arcane Devices}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Channeling]{Channeling}</td>\n<td>S, AB</td>\n<td>Reduce Power Point cost by 1 with a raise on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Activation]{Activation} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Extra Effort]{Extra Effort}</td>\n<td>S, AB (Gifted), Focus d6</td>\n<td>Increase @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Focus]{Focus} by +1 for 1 Power Point or +2 for 3 Power Points.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Finely Tuned]</td>\n<td>S, Artificer, Sm d8, Crafting d8</td>\n<td>Reduce the cost of creating @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Devices]{Arcane Devices}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Focus]</td>\n<td>S, AB, Sp d6, arcane skill d8</td>\n<td>If the wizard is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} from failing to cast a spell, they get an automatic roll to unshake at &ndash;2.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Focus]</td>\n<td>H, Focus</td>\n<td>If the wizard is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} from failing to cast a spell, the get an automatic roll to unshake.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Holy/Unholy Warrior]{Holy/Unholy Warrior}</td>\n<td>S, AB (Miracles), Faith d6</td>\n<td>Add +1 to +4 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak Rolls} for each Power Point spent.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Imbue Item]</td>\n<td>S, AB (Magecraft), Magecraft d6</td>\n<td>Spend 3 Power Points to create a device that replicates another power.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Holy/Unholy Warrior]{Holy/Unholy Warrior}</td>\n<td>S, AB (Miracles), Faith d6</td>\n<td>Add +1 to +4 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak Rolls} for each Power Point spent.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Mentalist]{Mentalist}</td>\n<td>S, AB (Psionics), Psionics d6</td>\n<td>+2 to opposed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Psionics]{Psionics} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.New Powers]{New Powers}</td>\n<td>N, AB</td>\n<td>Your character knows two new powers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Spell Finesse]</td>\n<td>N, AB, Arcana d8, arcane skill d8</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Strong Caster]</td>\n<td>S, AB, Sm d6, Sp d6, V d8</td>\n<td>Ignore up to 1 point of casting penalties.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Strong Caster]</td>\n<td>H, Concentration</td>\n<td>Ignore up to 2 points of casting penalties.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Wizard]{Wizard}</td>\n<td>S, AB (Magic), Spellcasting d6</td>\n<td>Spend 1 extra Power Point to change a spell&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trapping}.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Professional Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Ace]{Ace}</td>\n<td>N, A d8</td>\n<td>Character may spend @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak} damage for his vehicle and ignores up to 2 points of penalties.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Acrobat]{Acrobat}</td>\n<td>N, A d8, Athletics d8</td>\n<td>Free reroll on acrobatic @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} attempts.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Combat Acrobat]{Combat Acrobat}</td>\n<td>S, Acrobat</td>\n<td>&minus;1 to hit with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Attacks]{ranged and melee attacks}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Assassin]{Assassin}</td>\n<td>N, A d8, Fighting d6, Stealth d8</td>\n<td>+2 to damage foes when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} or assassin has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Boarder]</td>\n<td>N, Athletics d8+, Boating d6+</td>\n<td>All @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} rolls on ropes are made with a +2 bonus. Receives a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} if he is the first boarding an enemy vessel.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Entertainer]</td>\n<td>N, Performance d8</td>\n<td>+1 to any two \"bard\" skills.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Explorer]</td>\n<td>N, V d6, Survival d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival} and to resist the effects of heat and cold enviroments.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Familiar]</td>\n<td>N, AB (Magic) Arcana d8</td>\n<td>The mage acquires an animal familiar.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Guardian]</td>\n<td>N, A d8, Fighting d6, Notice d6</td>\n<td>Attacks aimed at a chosen charge are rolled against the guardian.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Holy Adept]</td>\n<td>N, AB (Miracles), Faith d8, Fighting d8</td>\n<td>The adept adds a d4 to unarmed attacks and can activate a power on themselves as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Investigator]{Investigator}</td>\n<td>N, Sm d8, Research d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research} and certain types of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Jack-Of-All-Trades]{Jack-Of-All-Trades}</td>\n<td>N, Sm d10</td>\n<td>Gain d4 in a skill (or d6 with a raise) until replaced.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Knight]</td>\n<td>N, Sp d6, St d8, v d8, Fighting d8, Riding d8</td>\n<td>The knight is gifted with the tools of his trade. He also gains a +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls when dealing with good causes.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Storyteller]</td>\n<td>S, Sm d8, Persuasion d8</td>\n<td>The storyteller rolls d8's for Glory rolls instead of d6's.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Legendary Storyteller]</td>\n<td>H, Master Storyteller</td>\n<td>The storyteller gains a d8 Glory for each raise after the first.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Monster Hunter]</td>\n<td>S, Sp d6</td>\n<td>The hero is immune to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks of one type of creature.&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Mr Fix It]{Mr. Fix It}</td>\n<td>N, Repair d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Repair]{Repair} rolls, half the time required with a raise.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Necromancer]</td>\n<td>N, AB (magic or Miracles) Sp d8, arcane skill d8</td>\n<td>May cast @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Zombie]{Zombie} as a Novice. Additional, reduce the cost of casting and extend the duration.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Master Necromancer]</td>\n<td>V, Necromancer</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Zombie]{Zombies} raised by Necromancer gain an extra die in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and one skill of his choice.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rope Monkey]</td>\n<td>S, A d8, Athletics d10</td>\n<td>The sailor can swing among the rigging to move around a ship or canopy. They may also make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll if they fall to take half damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Scholar]{Scholar}</td>\n<td>N, Research d8</td>\n<td>+2 to any one &ldquo;knowledge&rdquo; skill.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Skald]</td>\n<td>N, Performance d6</td>\n<td>+2 to any one \"skald\" skill.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Soldier]{Soldier}</td>\n<td>N, S d6, V d6</td>\n<td>Strength is one die type higher for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Gear Notes]{Encumbrance} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Minimum Strength]{Min Str}. Reroll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls when resisting environmental @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hazards]{Hazards}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Tinkerer]</td>\n<td>S, Crafting d8, Magecraft d10</td>\n<td>The artificer may craft an item that adds a +1 bonus to a relevant @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{trait} roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Thief]{Thief}</td>\n<td>N, A d8, Stealth&nbsp;d6, Thievery d6</td>\n<td>+1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Thievery]{Thievery}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} rolls made to climb, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} in urban environments.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Woodsman]{Woodsman}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d6, Survival d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} in the wilds.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Racial Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Adamantine Body]</td>\n<td>N, Warforged</td>\n<td>Start with +4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bladedancer]</td>\n<td>N, Elf, A d8, Fighting d8, Two-Fisted</td>\n<td>Make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{run} roll, and get a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack at everything in his path.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Extra Shifter Ability]</td>\n<td>N, Shifter</td>\n<td>Gains one additional shifting ability.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Healing Factor]</td>\n<td>N, Shifter, V d8</td>\n<td>Free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak roll} on any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} when ending shifting.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Overload Metabolism]</td>\n<td>N, Warforged, A d8, Str d8</td>\n<td>Once per session make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll to repair one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}. two on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. Reduce @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} one die type for 10 minutes.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Primal Fury]</td>\n<td>S, Half-orc or ORc, Berserk</td>\n<td>May spend a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to activate @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Berserk]{Berserk}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Primal Fury]</td>\n<td>V, Primal Fury, Sp d8</td>\n<td>No penalty to end rage, and the hero will not hit an ally on a Critical Failure with her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} die.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Psicrystal]</td>\n<td>N, Kalashtar, SB (Psionics), Sm d8</td>\n<td>Allows the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Kalashtar]{Kalashtar} to have a fragment of thier personality placed into a srystalline construct with some abilities.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Psiforged Body]</td>\n<td>N, Warforged, AB (Psionics)</td>\n<td>This adds 5 Powers Points for a Psionic Warforged.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Reactive Shifting]</td>\n<td>N, Shifter, Quick</td>\n<td>Shifters can shift as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} even when not on their turn.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Running Throw</td>\n<td>S, Bugbear, Half-orc, or Orc, Str d8, Athletics d8</td>\n<td>The hero moves at least half their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} and throws a weapon may increase their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{range} by 2/4/8.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Scamper]</td>\n<td>S, Halfling, A d8</td>\n<td>Opponents larger than the hero subtract 1 from their attack rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Scamper]</td>\n<td>V, Scamper</td>\n<td>Opponents get no @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Ganging Up]{gang up} on the hero.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Shieldwall]</td>\n<td>S, Hobogoblin, Block</td>\n<td>The hero can add his shield modifier to an adjacent ally.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Shifter Stamina]</td>\n<td>N, Shifter</td>\n<td>The adventurer is immune to nonlethal damage and the effects of fatigue while they are shifted.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sunder]</td>\n<td>S, Dwarf</td>\n<td>The adventurer ignores 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{armor}, or 2 points on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} of the attack roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Sunder]</td>\n<td>V, Sunder</td>\n<td>The hero ignores 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{armor}, or 4 points on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} of the attack roll.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.War Cry]</td>\n<td>S, Bugbear, Half-orc, or Orc, Intimidation d8</td>\n<td>Once per turn, affect all foes in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template} with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Social Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Bolster]{Bolster}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>May remove @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted or Vulnerable} state after a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Common Bond]{Common Bond}</td>\n<td>WC, N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>The hero may freely give her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to others.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Connections]{Connections}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>Contacts provide aid or other favors once per session.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Humiliate]{Humiliate}</td>\n<td>N, Taunt d8</td>\n<td>Free reroll when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Menacing]{Menacing}</td>\n<td>N, See Text</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Provoke]{Provoke}</td>\n<td>N, Taunt d6</td>\n<td>May &ldquo;provoke&rdquo; foes with a raise on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} roll. See text.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Rabble-Rouser]{Rabble-Rouser}</td>\n<td>S, Spirit d8</td>\n<td>Once per turn, affect all foes in a Medium Blast Template with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Reliable]{Reliable}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Free reroll when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} rolls.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Retort]{Retort}</td>\n<td>N, Taunt d6</td>\n<td>A raise when resisting a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} attack makes the foe @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Streetwise]{Streetwise}</td>\n<td>N, Sm d6</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} and criminal networking.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Strong Willed]{Strong Willed}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>+2 to resist @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts or Spirit}-based @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Iron Will]{Iron Will}</td>\n<td>S, Brave, Strong Willed</td>\n<td>The bonus now applies to resisting and recovery from powers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Work The Room]{Work The Room}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Once per turn, roll a second die when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Supporting} via @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} and apply result to additional ally.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Work the Crowd]{Work the Crowd}</td>\n<td>S, Work the Room</td>\n<td>As above, but up to twice per turn.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Weird Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Beast Bond]{Beast Bond}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>The hero may spend @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} for animals under her control.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Beast Master]{Beast Master}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>Animals like your hero and he has a pet of some sort. See text.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Champion]{Champion}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8, Fighting d6</td>\n<td>+2 damage vs. supernaturally evil creatures.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Chi]{Chi}</td>\n<td>V, Martial Warrior</td>\n<td>Once per combat, reroll failed attack, make enemy reroll successful attack, or add +d6 to unarmed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Danger Sense]{Danger Sense}</td>\n<td>N</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll at +2 to sense ambushes or similar events.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Healer]{Healer}</td>\n<td>N, Sp d8</td>\n<td>+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Healing]{Healing} rolls, magical or otherwise.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Liquid Courage]{Liquid Courage}</td>\n<td>N, V d8</td>\n<td>Alcohol increases @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} a die type and ignores one level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound penalties}; &ndash;1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility, Smarts}, and related skills.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Scavenger]{Scavenger}</td>\n<td>N, Luck</td>\n<td>May find a needed item once per encounter.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Storm Chaser]</td>\n<td>N, Boating or Piloting d8</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} during storms. Recieve extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} during @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chases}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Symbiont Mastery]</td>\n<td>N, Sp d6</td>\n<td>Recieve +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} in battle of wills with sybionts. With symbiont attached, +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak rolls}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wind Sense]</td>\n<td>N, Sm d8, Boating or Piloting d8</td>\n<td>+1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Boating]{Boating} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Piloting]{Piloting} during Contact. Recieve extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} during @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Chases and Vehicles]{Chases}.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table class=\"table summary-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Legendary Edges</h2>\n</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Edge</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Requirements</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Summary</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Followers]{Followers}</td>\n<td>WC, L</td>\n<td>The hero has five followers.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Professional]{Professional}</td>\n<td>L, Max Trait</td>\n<td>The character&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} and its limit increases one step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Expert]{Expert}</td>\n<td>L, Professional in Trait</td>\n<td>The character&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} and its limit increases one step.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Master]{Master}</td>\n<td>WC, L, Expert in Trait</td>\n<td>The character&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Wild Die} is a d10 with a chosen @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait}.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Improved Enchant]</td>\n<td>L, Enchant</td>\n<td>Allows the artificer to craft major artifacts.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Sidekick]{Sidekick}</td>\n<td>WC, L</td>\n<td>The character gains a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card} sidekick.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Tough As Nails]{Tough As Nails}</td>\n<td>L, V d8</td>\n<td>The hero can take four @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} before being Incapacitated.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Tougher Than Nails]{Tougher Than Nails}</td>\n<td>L, Tough as Nails, V d12</td>\n<td>The hero can take five @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} before being Incapacitated.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Weapon Master]{Weapon Master}</td>\n<td>L, Fighting d12</td>\n<td>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Parry} increases by +1 and Fighting bonus damage die is d8.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"improved-edge\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Master of Arms]{Master of Arms}</td>\n<td>L, Weapon Master</td>\n<td>Parry increases another +1 and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{bonus damage} die is d10.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</figure>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","_id":"v5jwktj15g266SNC"}
