{"name":"Rituals","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_3t20aa8en26","path":"Savage Eberron Rules#/CF_SEP/4. Magic#/CF_SEP/4.1. Using Magic","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Rituals</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>While magic is potent and prevelant throughout all of society in Khorvaire, the most powerful magics are performed through rituals, allowing a magician to gather magical energies to unleash. To perform a ritual the magician must first know the power or have access to a tome providing the instructions to the ritual. In addition, it is wise to have a location where he can work without disruption.</p>\n<p>Activating a power via ritual is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dramatic Tasks]{Dramatic Task} using the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill}&nbsp; and the caster needs to accumulate five successes/raises within five rounds. The last roll, the one achieving the fifth success, determines the spell&rsquo;s effect. If opposed, the final roll is the only one the target(s) roll against.</p>\n<p>For powers known to the caster, the time for each \"action\" (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dramatic Tasks]) is one minute per final Casting Modifier of the spell, including any power modifiers (see below). Abilities which reduce the Casting Modifier, such as Edges or special abilities of an Arcane Background, do not apply unless specifically stated to affect rituals. The Casting Modifier does not apply to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll unless the magician chooses to perform the ritual faster. A caster can reduce the time per action by one minute for each &minus;1 Casting Modifier applied to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} rolls to a minimum of one minute per action.</p>\n<h3>Components</h3>\n<p>A wizard requires one component per Rank of the power being cast. Should he not have enough, he suffers a &minus;1 penalty to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} (not a Casting Modifier) per component he is short. Ritual components must be of higher quality and cost ten galifars (gp) each.</p>\n<h3>Disruption</h3>\n<p>Rituals may be disrupted as any power, and the primary caster may end an active ritual as a free action.</p>\n<h3>Range</h3>\n<p>Powers with a Range greater than Touch double their Range automatically when cast via ritual. Powers with a Range of Touch or Self gain a Range of Smarts.</p>\n<h3>Power Modifiers</h3>\n<p>The caster can choose additional benefits by increasing the Casting Modifier from the available @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{power modifiers} for magic. However a few of the modifiers have different Casting Modifiers or benefits when applied to a ritual casting.</p>\n<h3>Preparation and Assistance</h3>\n<p>Using additional casters or sacrificing resources make rituals easier to complete.</p>\n<p><strong>Additional Casters:</strong> Assistants with the same Arcane Background may aid the caster by making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{support} rolls at each step using their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} as long as they possess the power. If they do not possess the power, they may still assist but suffer a &minus;2 penalty to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll. If a Casting Modifier is applied, assistants suffer the same penalty to their skill roll as the lead caster.</p>\n<p><strong>Rare Components:</strong> By using more expensive, unique, and rare components the Casting Modifier can be reduced. The caster must replace all the necessary components to gain the benefit and as usual, the components are used up regardless of the ritual&rsquo;s outcome.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>At a cost of 50 galifars (gp) for each component, the caster ignores a &minus;1 penalty.</li>\n<li>At a cost of 150 galifars (gp) for each component, the caster ignores a &minus;2 penalty.</li>\n<li>At a cost of 500 galifars (gp) for each component, the caster ignores a &minus;4 penalty.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Failure</h3>\n<p>Failing a ritual incurs normal Backlash to the caster and any participants for their Arcane Background. If the failure occurs on a Complication (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dramatic Tasks]), the caster and participants suffer 2d6 damage, ignoring armor.</p>\n<h3>Unknown Rituals</h3>\n<p>A wizard may also perform rituals for powers he does not know, provided he has detailed instructions, sometimes found on scrolls or in ancient tomes. The ritual power must be on the caster's allowed list, though it may be of a higher Rank.</p>\n<p>The magician must first figure out how to perform the ritual by making an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Arcana] roll. He suffers a &minus;2 penalty per Rank of the power past Novice to the roll (&minus;2 for Seasoned, &minus;4 for Veteran, and so on) and may only attempt the roll once per day. On a critical failure, he can't attempt to decipher the ritual again until he gains an Advance. Performing a ritual for an unknown power otherwise works the same, but Casting Modifiers are doubled.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Articles on the Use of Magic</h2>\n<div class=\"swade-columns\">\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Arcane Backgrounds}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Power Modifiers]{Powers Modifiers}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Powers Summary List]{Powers Summary list}</h3>\n<h3>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Rituals]{Rituals}</h3>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/logo-eberron-circle-black.webp","_id":"ypyzDxOrWPcG0PFo"}
